quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  16,112,"And Allāh presents an example: a city [i.e., Makkah] which was safe and secure, its provision coming to it in abundance from every location, but it denied the favors of Allāh. So Allāh made it taste the envelopment of hunger and fear for what they had been doing."
  16,113,"And there had certainly come to them a Messenger from among themselves, but they denied him; so punishment overtook them while they were wrongdoers."
  16,114,"Then eat of what Allāh has provided for you [which is] lawful and good. And be grateful for the favor of Allāh, if it is [indeed] Him that you worship."
  17,79,"And from [part of] the night, pray{1} with it [i.e., recitation of the Qur’ān] as additional [worship] for you; it is expected that{2} your Lord will resurrect you to a praised station.{3}",footnotes:1:Literally, \"arise from sleep for prayer.\",footnotes:2:This is a promise from Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā) to Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ).,footnotes:3:The position of intercession by permission of Allāh and the highest degree in Paradise.
  17,80,"And say, ",footnotes:1:Into Madīnah at the time of emigration, or into the grave.,footnotes:2:From Makkah, or from the grave at the time of resurrection.
  17,81,"And say, "
  18,46,"Wealth and children are [but] adornment of the worldly life. But the enduring good deeds are better to your Lord{1} for reward and better for [one's] hope.",footnotes:1:i.e., in His sight or evaluation.
  18,47,"And [warn of] the Day when We will remove the mountains and you will see the earth exposed,{1} and We will gather them and not leave behind from them anyone.",footnotes:1:i.e., flattened and bare.
  18,48,"And they will be presented before your Lord in rows, [and He will say], "
  19,7,"[He was told],{1} ",footnotes:1:By Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā) through the angels.
  19,8,"He said, "
  19,9,"[An angel] said, "